<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Learn DSA</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <%- include('../../partials/head') %>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="d-flex">
      <%- include('../../partials/sidebar') %>

      <main class="flex-fill p-4">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h3>Red-Black Trees</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Red-Black Trees — Introduction

            A **Red-Black Tree** is a self-balancing Binary Search Tree.

            It ensures that the tree remains approximately balanced, so operations are efficient.

            ### Key Operations
            - Search
            - Insert
            - Delete

            ####Time Complexity####
            ####O(log n)####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[10] --> B[5];
              A --> C[15];
              B --> D[3];
              B --> E[7];
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Properties of Red-Black Trees

            A Red-Black Tree follows these rules:

            1. Each node is either **red** or **black**
            2. The root is always **black**
            3. No two red nodes can be adjacent
            4. Every path from root to leaf has the same number of black nodes

            ####Balanced Height####
            ####h <= 2 * log(n + 1)####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[Black] --> B[Red];
              A --> C[Red];
              B --> D[Black];
              C --> E[Black];
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Node Structure

            Each node stores:

            - Value (key)
            - Color (Red or Black)
            - Left and Right children
            - Parent reference

            ####Node Representation####
            ####Node = (key, color, left, right, parent)####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[Node] --> B[Key];
              A --> C[Color];
              A --> D[Left];
              A --> E[Right];
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Insertion in Red-Black Trees

            Steps:
            1. Insert node like a BST (as red)
            2. Fix violations of Red-Black properties
            3. Use:
              - Recoloring
              - Rotations (left/right)

            ####Goal####
            ####Maintain balance and properties####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[Insert Node] --> B[Check Violations];
              B --> C[Recolor];
              B --> D[Rotate];
              C --> E[Balanced Tree];
              D --> E;
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Rotations and Balancing

            Rotations help maintain balance:

            - **Left Rotation**
            - **Right Rotation**

            They restructure the tree without breaking BST rules.

            ####Rotation Effect####
            ####Preserves order, improves balance####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A[Unbalanced] --> B[Rotation];
              B --> C[Balanced];
              C --> D[Valid RB Tree];
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <!-- CONTROLS --> 
        <div class="nav-controls"> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark me-2" id="prev">← Prev</button> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark" id="next">Next →</button> 
        </div> 
        <div class="progress-container"> 
          <div class="progress-bar" id="progress"></div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide-counter"> 
          <span id="current">1</span>/<span id="total">1</span> 
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
